47. , http://www.jma.go.jp/jma/jma-eng/jma-center/Climate_Change/chap_4.pdf, Japan Meteorological Agency Japan Meteorological Agency, Tokyo. Also available at; Kondratyev, K.Y., Varotsos, C., (2000) Atmospheric Ozone Variability, p. 617. , Springer Tokyo; Labitzke, K., The global signal of the 11-year solar cycle in the atmosphere: When do we need the QBO? (2003) Met Z, 12, pp. 209-216. , 10.1127/0941-2948/2003/0012-0211; Lee, S., Choi, G., Lim, H., Lee, J., Global and regional distribution of carbon monoxide from MOPIT: Seasonal distribution at 700 hPa (2004) Environ Monit Assess, 92, pp. 35-42. , 10.1023/B:EMAS.0000014507.31728.48; Logan, J.A., An analysis of ozonesonde data for the lower stroposphere: Recommendation for testing models (1999) J Geophys Res, 104, pp. 16151-16170. , 10.1029/1999JD900216; Logan, J.A., An analysis of ozonesonde data for the troposphere: Recommendations for testing 3-D models and development of a gridded climatology for tropospheric ozone (1999) J Geophys Res, 104, pp. 16115-16149. , 10.1029/1998JD100096; Logan, J.A., Megretskaia, I.A., Miller, A.J., Tiao, G.C., Choi, D., Zhang, L., Stolarski, R.S., Uchino, O., Trends in the vertical distribution of ozone: A comparison of two analyses of ozonesonde data (1999) J Geophys Res, 104, pp. 26373-26399. , 10.1029/1999JD900300; Maindonald, J., Braun, J., (2004) Data Analysis and Graphics Using R: An Example-based Approach, p. 362. , Cambridge University Press Cambridge, UK; Naja, M., Akimoto, H., Contribution of regional pollution and long-range transport to the Asia-Pacific region: Analysis of long-term ozonesonde data over Japan (2004) J Geophys Res, 109. , (doi: 10.1029/2004JD004687); Naja, M., Akimoto, H., Staehelin, J., Ozone in background and photochemically aged air over central Europe: Analysis of long-term ozonesonde data from Hohenpeissenberg and Payerne (2003) J Geophys Res, 108, p. 4063. , 10.1029/2002JD002477; Newell, R.E., Wu, Z.-X., Zhu, Y., Hu, W., Browell, E.V., Gregory, G.L.,